<title>PORTUGAL: BCI surges as bank plans to leave bourse.</title>
<headline>BCI surges as bank plans to leave bourse.</headline>
<dateline>LISBON 1996-10-22</dateline>
<text>
<p>Shares in Banco de Comercio e Industria (BCI) rose 14 percent on the Lisbon bourse after news that the Portuguese bank's next extraordinary meeting will discuss removing the share from its listing on the bourse, dealers said.</p>
<p>&quot;BCI shares shot up due to news that the next extraordinary meeting will discuss the departure of the bank from the bourse,&quot; one dealer said.</p>
<p>BCI stood at 1,040 escudos, up 130, in volume of 23,686 shares at 0950 GMT.</p>
